Dmitry Goncharov a.k.a. Dima Stuff was born in Weimar, one of the oldest cultural centers of Western Europe. He fell in love with music in his childhood and till nowadays music plays a significant part in his life. Technological process which accompanied Dmitry’s maturing gave him the opportunity to start his own musical experiments. Dmitry’s first steps towards the hip-hop scene were quite successful and inspired him to continue experiments in other styles of electronic music. First results of these experiments formed the basis of “House Corporation” duo inspired mainly by Dima Stuff. Duo’s tracks quickly got into rotation of one of the best radio stations of Ukraine – Kiss FM. At that time duo’s house-electro-techno sound evolved rapidly enforcing Dmitry to start his own DJ career and become a resident DJ in a local night club. Successful Electro Night parties in the best night club of the city were his next step and it gave Dmitry the opportunity to master his musical and DJ skills being inspired by the energy of the dancefloor. But the time keeps running and Dmitry’s sound changes and becomes more and more interesting in spite of “House Corporation” duo ceased its existence. Dmitry meets young and talented producer Oleg Gorovoi a.k.a. DJ Reaver and their acquaintance quickly transforms into creative collaboration which efforts were noticed by DJ Beauty, one of the key persons of Ukrainian club scene. She included duo’s “Mint Foq” track into her compilation “Bigudi” which was released on popular Ukrainian label “Virus Music”. Among the tracks on this compilation was the remix of Reaver & D.Stuff’s “Milk Rain” released on DS Records. In the nearest time Dmirty’s remix of “Ghost” by Vincent Rio & Vladimir Great is to be released on Send Records. Presently Dmitry tends to minimal-electro-techno sound collaborating with Ukrainian and foreign musicians.
